conditional hypothesis: significant decline in low-complexity reefs and stability in high-complexity reefs."},{"id":"D","text":"In both highly complex and simple reefs, native teleost populations decreased by approximately $25\\%$ within six months of the introduction of invasive lionfish species, which restates table values without connecting them to the hypothesis in the passage.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Unconditional Support Decoy] Shows decline in both reef types, ignoring the required buffering effect of structural complexity."}]'::jsonb, 'C', 'Step 1 — State the claim
